// Unified Cloudflare Worker for the musicians app (locked Phase A runtime
// decision — see apps/musicians/CLAUDE.md). Unlike its siblings
// wrangler.jsonc / wrangler.chords.jsonc (assets-ONLY: scales + chords are
// static SPAs deployed to Workers Static Assets), this app is the first with
// a backend, so it carries BOTH a Worker `main` entry (the `/api/*` BFF +
// HTMLRewriter OG injection) AND an `assets` binding for the SPA.
//
// Routing: no `run_worker_first` — Cloudflare serves a request directly from
// `assets` only when it matches a built file; everything else (the `/api/*`
// endpoints, `/sitemap.xml`, and `/musicians/:id` document navigations needing
// per-request OG) has no matching file and so reaches the Worker's `fetch`,
// which then either handles it or hands off to `env.ASSETS` (with
// `not_found_handling: "single-page-application"` serving index.html 200 for
// React Router). This is exactly the contract worker/index.ts is tested
// against (worker/index.test.ts). `compatibility_date` matches the siblings.
//
// Secrets (NEO4J_*) are NEVER here — Cloudflare project env + local `.dev.vars`
// only (landmine 12). Deploy is USER-GATED (landmine 14); the out-of-repo
// dashboard steps are in apps/musicians/docs/deploy-checklist.md.
{
  "$schema": "node_modules/wrangler/config-schema.json",
  "name": "jazzlore-musicians",
  "compatibility_date": "2026-05-12",
  "main": "./apps/musicians/worker/index.ts",
  "assets": {
    "directory": "./apps/musicians/dist",
    "binding": "ASSETS",
    "not_found_handling": "single-page-application"
  }
}
